SIMPLE: terrane
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Terrane
<hw>Ter"rane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>terrain</ets>, from L. <ets>terra</ets> earth.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A group of rocks having a common age or origin;
-- nearly equivalent to <xex>formation</xex>, but used somewhat less
comprehensively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Terrane</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Terrane
<hw>Ter"rane</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geog.)</fld> <sn>2.</sn> <def>A
region or limited area considered with reference to some special
feature; <as>as, the <ex>terrane</ex> of a river, that is, its drainage
basin</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Terrapin</ent>⟦br⟧
